Rating: 3
Great, fresh-tasting, light summer salad option that I initially feared because of the "Waldorf-esque" ingredients. I was pleasantly surprised. Good use for leftover chicken, even if it is grilled/braised/barBQ'd (poached may be a bit on the bland side). I didn't have Boston bibb lettuce and just tore up green leaf lettuce, actually tossed it with the vinaigrette rather than "drizzle". Good, easy, flavorful dish that is an entire meal in itself. Will be making this again.

