Rating: 4
My husband said this is now his favorite salad...... grilling the chicken made a huge difference. I'll try the suggested marinades next time.

Rating: 3
I changed this substantially and it ended up being excellent. I cut the chicken into small chunks and then let it marinate in some olive oil, lemon juice, white wine, garlic, salt, pepper and onion powder for about half an hour. I then pan seared it in a combo of olive oil and butter. I added some cider vinegar to the dressing and a dash of salt I added a combination of fresh feta and fresh mozzarella to the salad as well as some arugula. The end result was to die for!

